openapi: 3.0.0 info: contact: email: info@kedlin.com name: Call Control url: https://www.callcontrol.com/documentation description: API for blocking phone calls with Call Control. Data is from crowdsourced community blacklist from 12+ million users and government agencies (FTC, FCC, IRS) Try with api_key 'demo', hit explore above, and then try phone numbers 18008472911,13157244022,17275567300,18008276655,12061231234. title: Call Control version: 2015-11-01 x-apisguru-categories: - telecom x-logo: backgroundColor: "#FFFFFF" url: https://twitter.com/CallControlLLC/profile_image?size=original x-origin: - format: swagger url: https://www.callcontrol.com/js/swagger/swagger.json version: "2.0" x-providerName: callcontrol.com paths: "/api/2015-11-01/Complaints/{phoneNumber}": get: deprecated: false description: "This is the main funciton to get data out of the call control reporting system
\r \ Try with api_key 'demo' and phone numbers 18008472911, 13157244022, 17275567300, 18008276655, and 12061231234 (last one not spam)" operationId: Complaints_Complaints parameters: - description: phone number to search in: path name: phoneNumber required: true schema: type: string responses: "200": description: OK content: application/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/Complaints" text/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/Complaints" summary: "Complaints: Free service (with registration), providing community and government complaint lookup by phone number for up to 2,000 queries per month. Details include number complaint rates from (FTC, FCC, IRS, Indiana Attorney General) and key entity tag extractions from complaints." tags: - Complaints "/api/2015-11-01/Enterprise/GetUser/{phoneNumber}": get: deprecated: false description: "" operationId: EnterpriseApi_GetUser parameters: - in: path name: phoneNumber required: true schema: type: string responses: "200": description: User Object content: application/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/CallControlUser" text/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/CallControlUser" "400": description: Bad request (invalid phone number) summary: "Enterprise GET: GetUser\r Returns the current information from the user; try 12066194123 as demo" tags: - EnterpriseApi "/api/2015-11-01/Enterprise/ShouldBlock/{phoneNumber}/{userPhoneNumber}": get: deprecated: false description: "This returns information required to perform basic call blocking behaviors\r \ Try with api_key 'demo' and phone numbers 18008472911, 13157244022, 17275567300, 18008276655, and 12061231234 (last one not spam)" operationId: EnterpriseApi_ShouldBlock parameters: - description: phone number to search in: path name: phoneNumber required: true schema: type: string - description: (OPTIONAL) phone number of user to look up block rules in: path name: userPhoneNumber required: true schema: type: string responses: "200": description: true(block) false (no block) content: application/json: schema: enum: - allow - voiceMail - block type: string text/json: schema: enum: - allow - voiceMail - block type: string "400": description: Bad request (invalid phone number) summary: "Enterprise GET: ShouldBlock\r Simple Enteprise which returns a call block proceed decision." tags: - EnterpriseApi /api/2015-11-01/Enterprise/UpsertUser: post: deprecated: false operationId: EnterpriseApi_UpsertUser requestBody: content: application/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/CallControlUser" text/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/CallControlUser" description: "[FromBody] User \r \ This returns information required to perform basic call blocking behaviors. The demo key will return ok, but will not save the data.
" required: true responses: "200": description: Ok content: application/json: schema: type: object text/json: schema: type: object "400": description: Bad request (eg. invalid phone nubmer) summary: "UpsertUser: insert or update all properties from a user\r PhoneNumber\r WhiteList (list of phone numbers to whitelist)\r BlackList (list of phone numbers to blacklist)\r QuietHourList (list of quiet hour objects)\r UseCommunityBlacklist (enable / disable community blacklist) default true\r BreakThroughQhWithMultipleCalls (break through quiet hours with two calls in 3 minutes)\r WhiteListBreaksQh (break through quiet hours for whitelist)" tags: - EnterpriseApi /api/2015-11-01/Report: post: deprecated: false description: "This returns information required to perform basic call blocking behaviors
\r \ Try with api_key 'demo' and phone numbers 18008472911, 13157244022, 17275567300, 18008276655, and 12061231234 (last one not spam)" operationId: Reputation_Report requestBody: content: application/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/CallReport" text/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/CallReport" description: "[FromBody] Call Report\r \ PhoneNumber, \r \ Caller name(optional), \r \ Call category(optional), \r \ Comment or tags(free text) (optional), \r \ Unwanted call - yes/no(optional)," required: true responses: "400": description: Bad request (eg. invalid phone nubmer) summary: "Report: report spam calls received to better tune our algorithms based upon spam calls you receive" tags: - Reputation "/api/2015-11-01/Reputation/{phoneNumber}": get: deprecated: false description: "This returns information required to perform basic call blocking behaviors
\r \ Try with api_key 'demo' and phone numbers 18008472911, 13157244022, 17275567300, 18008276655, and 12061231234 (last one not spam)" operationId: Reputation_Reputation parameters: - description: phone number to search in: path name: phoneNumber required: true schema: type: string responses: "200": description: Reputation information content: application/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/Reputation" text/json: schema: $ref: "#/components/schemas/Reputation" "400": description: Bad request (invalid phone number) summary: "Reputation:\r Premium service which returns a reputation informaiton of a phone number via API." tags: - Reputation servers: - url: https://api.callcontrol.com components: securitySchemes: apiKey: description: API Key Authentication in: header name: apiKey type: apiKey schemas: CallControlUser: properties: Age: format: int32 type: integer BlackList: items: type: string type: array BlockBehavior: enum: - allow - voiceMail - block type: string BreakThroughQhWithMultipleCalls: type: boolean Email: type: string FirstName: type: string Gender: type: string LastName: type: string MiddleName: type: string PhoneNumbeRegion: type: string PhoneNumber: type: string QuietHourList: items: $ref: "#/components/schemas/QuietHour" type: array Salutation: type: string Suffix: type: string UseCommunityBlacklist: type: boolean WhiteList: items: type: string type: array WhiteListBreaksQh: type: boolean type: object CallReport: description: "Call Report\r PhoneNumber, \r Caller name(optional), \r Call category(optional), \r Comment or tags(free text) (optional), \r Unwanted call - Sunday - Monday - Tuesday - Wednesday - Thursday - Friday - Saturday type: string type: array DurationMin: format: int32 type: integer StartHourLocal: format: int32 type: integer StartMinLocal: format: int32 type: integer TimeZoneName: type: string type: object Reputation: properties: CallType: readOnly: true type: string Confidence: format: int32 type: integer IsSpam: type: boolean LastComplaintDate: format: date-time type: string ReportedCallerName: type: string Tags: items: type: string type: array type: object
